tn.org/', 'https://web.archive.org/web/20250815130556/https://hostingfest.net/', 'https://www.hig.se/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hostingfest', 'https://www.sgpbusiness.com/company/Ang-Brothers-Me-Pte-Ltd', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/ga%CC%88vle/1142576926', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/secretaria-municipal-de-sau%CC%81de-de-fortaleza/431949261', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/swiss-rose-factory/481426718']}}, {'title': 'Limiting access based on roles prevents non-admin users from affecting security and functionality.Read more 👉 https://lttr.ai/Aroiq#Security #Infosec #CloudSecurity', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 23:33:46 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@lbhuston/116660453004217460', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['lttr.ai'], 'email-addr': ['lbhuston@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'The DOJ subpoenaed Apple, Google, Amazon, and Walmart for the names, addresses, and purchase histories of 100,000+ people who downloaded a car diagnostics app.Not the actual target, just people who had an app on their phone.The company they actually want is in the Cayman Islands. So they went after the app stores instead.https://blog.ppb1701.com/the-app-store-is-a-dragnet#bigtech #privacy #surveillance #apple #google #amazon #walmart #doj #appstore #userhostile #infosec #cleanairact #blog', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 23:33:46 +0000', 'source': 'https://ppb.social/@ppb1701/116660435675681194', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['blog.ppb1701.com']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2024-8310 - Critical auth bypass in OPW Fuel Management SiteSentinel. Full admin access. CVSS 9.8. No patch available. Isolate systems immediately. #CVE #infosec #OTsecurityhttps://www.valtersit.com/cve/CVE-2024-8310/', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 23:33:46 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@hugovalters/116660384999471199', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['valtersit.com'], 'email-addr': ['hugovalters@mastodon.social'], 'url': ['http://www.valtersit.com'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2024-8310']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-48557 - Spatie Laravel Media Library < 11.23.0 File Upload Restriction Bypass via FileAdder.php', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 20:16:28 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-48557', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Spatie Laravel Media Library before version 11.23.0 contains a file upload restriction bypass in FileAdder::defaultSanitizer(). The sanitizer checks only the final filename suffix, allowing double-extension filenames such as shell.php.jpg to bypass the blocklist, with pathinfo() preserving inner .php stems in saved filenames. The blocklist also omits executable extensions including .php6, .shtml, and .htaccess. The double-extension bypass requires a legacy Apache AddHandler configuration to achieve PHP execution; the incomplete blocklist bypass does not.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-48557vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-48557weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['608ea03703d3887c46434f5dda6af56de6346aba']}], 'url': ['http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/spatie-laravel-media-library-file-upload-restriction-bypass-via-fileadder-php', 'https://github.com/spatie/laravel-medialibrary/commit/608ea03703d3887c46434f5dda6af56de6346aba', 'https://github.com/spatie/laravel-medialibrary/pull/3939', 'https://github.com/spatie/laravel-medialibrary/releases/tag/11.23.0', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/spatie-laravel-media-library-file-upload-restriction-bypass-via-fileadder-php'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-48557']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-47266 - Formie: Unauthenticated front-end submission editing can overwrite existing submissions', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 20:16:28 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-47266', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Formie is a Craft CMS plugin for creating forms. Prior to 2.2.21 and 3.1.26, unauthenticated users could modify existing submissions by posting a known or guessed submission ID to formie/submissions/save-submission. This vulnerability is fixed in 2.2.21 and 3.1.26.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-47266vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-47266weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/verbb/formie/releases/tag/2.2.21', 'https://github.com/verbb/formie/releases/tag/3.1.26', 'https://github.com/verbb/formie/security/advisories/GHSA-pgxq-p76c-x9cg'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-47266', 'GHSA-PGXQ-P76C-X9CG']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-46527 - cpp-httplib: Malicious `X-Forwarded-For` Under Trusted-Proxy Configuration Triggers Empty `vector::front()`, Leading to Undefined Behavior and Server Crash', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 20:16:28 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-46527', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['cpp-httplib is a C++11 single-file header-only cross platform HTTP/HTTPS library. Prior to 0.44.0, When the server has called Server::set_trusted_proxies() with a non-empty trusted-proxy list, an attacker can send an HTTP request that includes an X-Forwarded-For header whose value parses to no valid IP segments. The code path then executes get_client_ip(), which calls front() on an empty std::vector—undefined behavior in C++. On typical implementations this manifests as abnormal process termination (denial of service). With Sanitizers enabled, you get an explicit runtime diagnostic. This vulnerability is fixed in 0.44.0.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-46527vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-46527weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/yhirose/cpp-httplib/security/advisories/GHSA-hg3g-vrg8-578g'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-46527', 'GHSA-HG3G-VRG8-578G']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-46385 - iskorotkov/avro: CPU Exhaustion in Avro Decoder', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 20:16:27 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-46385', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['iskorotkov/avro is a fast Go Avro codec. Prior to 2.33.0, the Avro array and map decoders looped over an attacker-controlled block-count value without checking the underlying reader\'s error state inside the loop body. Reader.ReadBlockHeader returns the count as a Go int, which is 64-bit on amd64 / arm64 targets — so a producer can declare a block of up to math.MaxInt64 (~9.2 × 10¹⁸) elements followed by EOF (or any truncated payload), and the decoder will attempt that many no-op iterations before propagating the error. The realistic ceiling is "indefinite until the worker is killed externally" — a single hostile payload pins a CPU core until the process is OOM-killed, deadline-cancelled, or terminated. Remote, unauthenticated denial-of-service. This vulnerability is fixed in 2.33.0.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-46385vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-46385weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/iskorotkov/avro/security/advisories/GHSA-w8j3-pq8g-8m7w'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-46385', 'GHSA-W8J3-PQ8G-8M7W']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-46384 - iskorotkov/avro: Integer Overflow in Avro Decoder', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 20:16:27 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-46384', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['iskorotkov/avro is a fast Go Avro codec. Prior to 2.33.0, several Avro decoder paths read attacker-controlled 64-bit values from the wire format and either narrowed them to platform-sized int before bounds-checking, or summed them with overflow-prone signed-int arithmetic. On 32-bit targets (GOARCH=386, arm, mips, wasm, etc.), the truncation paths can silently bypass byte-slice limits, select the wrong union branch, or hit the OCF negative-make panic via wrap. Three sub-issues are not 32-bit-specific: cumulative-size arithmetic overflow in arrayDecoder.Decode / mapDecoder.Decode / mapDecoderUnmarshaler.Decode (wraps at math.MaxInt64 on amd64 / arm64 and bypasses MaxSliceAllocSize / MaxMapAllocSize), math.MinInt negation in block-header handling, and make([]byte, size) with a negative size in OCF block reads — all three panic or bypass caps on any platform, giving an attacker a denial-of-service primitive there. This vulnerability is fixed in 2.33.0.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-46384vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-46384weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/iskorotkov/avro/security/advisories/GHSA-mc57-h6j3-3hmv'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-46384', 'GHSA-MC57-H6J3-3HMV']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-45697 - Formie: Pre-authenticated server-side template injection in Hidden fields', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 20:16:27 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-45697', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['Formie is a Craft CMS plugin for creating forms. Prior to 2.2.20 and 3.1.24, unauthenticated users could submit crafted values into Hidden fields (with Default value → Custom) that were evaluated as Twig during submission handling, which could lead to serious compromise of the Craft site (depending on template/sandbox behavior). This vulnerability is fixed in 2.2.20 and 3.1.24.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-45697vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-45697weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'email-addr': ['hey@cvefeed.io', 'security-advisories@github.com'], 'file': [{'hash_type': 'SHA-1', 'values': ['f690d5623163ce2a95da305238d6367575486ee3']}], 'url': ['https://github.com/verbb/formie/commit/f690d5623163ce2a95da305238d6367575486ee3', 'https://github.com/verbb/formie/releases/tag/2.2.20', 'https://github.com/verbb/formie/releases/tag/3.1.24', 'https://github.com/verbb/formie/security/advisories/GHSA-x7m9-mwc2-g6w2'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-45697', 'GHSA-X7M9-MWC2-G6W2']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2026-45372 - cpp-httplib: HTTP header value percent-decoding in server-side `parse_header` enables CRLF injection', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 20:16:26 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-45372', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ["cpp-httplib is a C++11 single-file header-only cross platform HTTP/HTTPS library. Prior to 0.44.0, when cpp-httplib's server parses an incoming request, it applies percent-decoding to every header value except Location and Referer. The validity check (is_field_value) is run before decoding, so encoded %0D%0A passes the check and is then expanded to a literal \\r\\n byte pair inside the stored header value. This vulnerability is fixed in 0.44.0.", 'The following products are affected byCVE-2026-45372vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2026-45372weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io'], 'email-addr': ['security-advisories@github.com'], 'url': ['https://github.com/yhirose/cpp-httplib/security/advisories/GHSA-xjxg-64p4-vj4m'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-45372', 'GHSA-XJXG-64P4-VJ4M']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans Centreon Web (29 mai 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/avis/CERTFR-2026-AVI-0659/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 1, 'text': ['De multiples vulnérabilités ont été découvertes dans Centreon Web. Elles permettent à un attaquant de provoquer une exécution de code arbitraire à distance et un contournement de la politique de sécurité.'], 'observables': {'url': ['https://thewatch.centreon.com/latest-security-bulletins-64/may-2026-monthly-security-bulletin-for-centreon-infra-monitoring-medium-5715']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans les produits Mattermost (29 mai 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000', 'source': 'https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/avis/CERTFR-2026-AVI-0660/', 'source_type': "['operational', 'vulnerabilities']", 'source_level': 1, 'text': [], 'observables': {'url': ['https://mattermost.com/security-updates/']}}, {'title': 'Multiples vulnérabilités dans Elastic Kibana (29 mai 2026)', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 29